# Mods

This is a list of mods I use. Listing them since some mods don't allow them to be added to a modpack.
## These all need [Fabric](https://fabricmc.net/) to work.

- **[3D Skin Layers](https://modrinth.com/mod/3dskinlayers)**
	- **🍀Quality of life mod** - 💻Client-side
	- Renders the player skin later in 3D

- **[Better F3](https://modrinth.com/mod/betterf3)**
	- **🍀Quality of life mod** - 💻Client-side
	- Replaces original debug HUD with a highly customizable, more readable HUD.

- **[Better Ping Display](https://modrinth.com/mod/better-ping-display-fabric)**
	 - **🍀Quality of life mod** - 💻Client-side
	 - Adds a configurable numerical ping display to the player list

- **[Continuity](https://modrinth.com/mod/continuity)**
	 - **🍀Quality of life mod** - 💻Client-side
	 -  Allows for efficient connected textures

- **[Entity Culling](https://modrinth.com/mod/entityculling)**
	- **⚡Optimization mod** - 💻Client-side
	- Using async path-tracing to hide Block-/Entities that are not visible

- **[Fabric API](https://modrinth.com/mod/fabric-api)**
	- **📕 Dependency / Library mod** - 💻Client or 🎛️ Server
	- Essential hooks for modding with Fabric.
	- Needed for many mods to work.

- **[Fabric Language Kotlin](https://modrinth.com/mod/fabric-language-kotlin)**
	- **📕 Dependency / Library mod** - 💻Client or 🎛️ Server
	- This is a mod that enables usage of the Kotlin programming language for Fabric mods.
	- Needed for many mods to work.

- **[Ferritecore](https://modrinth.com/mod/ferrite-core)**
	- **⚡Optimization mod** - 💻Client-side
	- Reduces the memory usage of Minecraft in a few different ways

- **[FPS Display](https://modrinth.com/mod/fpsdisplay)**
	 - **🍀Quality of life mod** - 💻Client-side
	 - Displays current FPS on-screen.

- **[ImmediatleyFast](https://modrinth.com/mod/immediatelyfast/)**
	 - **🍀Quality of life mod** - 💻Client-side
	 - Speed up immediate mode rendering in Minecraft

- **[]()**
